span.p:
MVC Pattern:
- Controllers manage API endpoints
- Models handle data and business logic
- Views (React components) render UI
➡️ Click to navigate to controller components

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Strategy Pattern:
- Different storage implementations (SQL)
- Common interface for extensibility
- Decouples data access from business logic
➡️ Click to see implementation details

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Factory Pattern:
- Service creation and abstraction
- Generator components creation
- Centralized object instantiation
➡️ Click to explore service factory methods

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Observer Pattern:
- State management in UI components
- Event-driven updates to canvas
- Reactive component rendering
➡️ Click to see observer implementations

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Layered Architecture:
- Clear separation between layers
- Dependency flow from top to bottom
- Encapsulation of implementation details
➡️ Click to explore architectural layers

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Separation of Concerns:
- Schema definitions separated from models
- LDL Schema independent from implementation
- Distinct responsibilities per component
➡️ Click to view separation boundaries
